Dictionary is a data structure that stores the information in key value pair.

In dictionary keys must be unique and immutable and values can be of any type of
data type whether they are mutable or immutable.

This makes dictionaries ideal for accessing data by a specific name rather than a 
numeric position like list.

Example :
a = {"x": 1, "y": 2}
print(a)

b = dict(name="Sam", age=20)
print(b)
